A Junonia coenia is a species of butterfly commonly known as the common buckeye.
The wingspan of this butterfly ranges from 4.5 to 6.4 cm.
The dorsal side of the wings have a brown-purple color, while the ventral side has bright and eye-catching patterns.
The wings have a slightly jagged outline with a scalloped edge.
The body of the butterfly is slim and elongated, with six legs and two antennas on its head.
Junonia coenia can be found in various habitats such as fields, gardens, marshes, and meadows.
They are known to migrate to southern areas during the winter months.
